Case 5-Asia-China-Shang-Zun-Bronze-1500 BCE

Formal Label:

Display Description:
'Zun' is a ritual wine vessel consisting of a jar with a widely flared lip supported on a tall footring. In the second half of the Shang the shouldered 'zun' was replaced by a taller columnar vessel based on the 'gu' and often designated as a cylindrical 'zun' (Rawson 1992).
LC Classification: NK7983.22

Date or Time Horizon: 1200 BCE
